DOS-PORT (patch 0080, Phase 9 wave 17.2). Re-authored standalone in
wave 17.3 to remove the wave-17.1 (patch 0079) instrumentation
dependency that the original 0080 carried. The cache logic is
unchanged; this version uses the bare _record_dirty_rect signature.

The wave-17.1 callsite-attribution investigation served its purpose
(found that no single callsite records a >50%-screen rect — the
coalesce cap-and-collapse merges ~80 small bg-tile rects every frame)
and has been removed (patch 0079 dropped). This patch keeps the lever
that came out of that investigation: replace map_draw_backdrop's
~80-tile-per-frame loop with a screen-sized cache populated once and
blitted as ONE drawSurface-equivalent call on subsequent frames.

A screen-sized SDL_Surface is allocated lazily and used as a cache for
the rendered-backdrop output. On a frame where the cache key matches
(same map, backdrop_id, scrolltype, parscroll_x/y, indexed_mode,
format, dimensions), the live tile loop is skipped and we blit the
cache to the window in a single SDL_BlitSurface call. On miss, tiles
are rendered INTO the cache surface (raw SDL_BlitSurface, no Renderer
overhead, no per-call dirty-rect record) and then blit to window.
Subsequent frames hit the cache.

For BK_FIXED scenes (intro cutscene curmap=72, static-bg game scenes)
parscroll is always 0,0 so the cache hits 100% after the first render.
For BK_PARALLAX / BK_FOLLOWFG, the cache hits whenever scrolling is
paused (player not moving) and misses when it's active — but a miss
still runs the same tile count as today (just into the cache instead
of the window) plus one final cache-to-window blit, so the miss path
is no worse than baseline. Cache hit beats baseline by ~80x on
drawcall count.

Three changes:

1. Renderer.h / Renderer.cpp: add Renderer::drawCachedBackdrop(SDL_Surface *)
   public method. The method validates window/src dimensions+format,
   drains any queued slow-path renderer commands, performs ONE
   SDL_BlitSurface to the window surface, bumps drawcall + records ONE
   full-screen dirty rect.

2. map.cpp: cache state + lifecycle wired into map_draw_backdrop.
   Lazy alloc on first miss; (re)alloc on dimension/format change;
   keyed match on the seven cache fields above; environment-variable
   killswitch (SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_BACKDROP_CACHE=0; strict '0' match
   per project env-var convention). map_flush_graphics() calls
   _backdrop_cache_reset() before deleting backdrop[] surfaces.

3. (Wave 17.3 will extend this scheme to the BK_FASTLEFT_LAYERS path
   used by the title screen, which currently bypasses this cache.)
---
 src/graphics/Renderer.cpp |  38 ++++++++
 src/graphics/Renderer.h   |  17 ++++
 src/map.cpp               | 179 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 3 files changed, 234 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
index 78d3d62..3f15ff7 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
+++ b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
@@ -3373,6 +3373,44 @@ void Renderer::blitPatternAcross(Surface *sfc, int x_dst, int y_dst, int y_src,
   } while (x < destwd);
 }
 
+// DOS-PORT (patch 0080, Phase 9 wave 17.2): cached-backdrop blit. See
+// Renderer.h for the contract. Single same-format SDL_BlitSurface
+// followed by ONE _record_dirty_rect call — replaces the ~80
+// drawSurface tile-loop emitted from map_draw_backdrop on every frame
+// before patch 0080. The dirty rect IS the whole screen (the bg layer
+// is unconditionally repainted), but the per-call overhead drops N→1.
+bool Renderer::drawCachedBackdrop(SDL_Surface *src)
+{
+  _DrawcallTimer _dct;  // patch 0060 — phase timing accumulator
+  if (!src || !_cached_window_surface) return false;
+  if (src->format != _cached_window_surface->format) return false;
+  if (src->w != _cached_window_surface->w ||
+      src->h != _cached_window_surface->h) return false;
+
+  // Drain any queued slow-path renderer commands so they reach the
+  // window surface before we overwrite the bg layer beneath them.
+  if (_renderer_queue_dirty)
+  {
+    SDL_FlushRenderer(_renderer);
+    _renderer_queue_dirty = false;
+  }
+
+  // Same-format INDEX8→INDEX8 (or RGB565→RGB565) → SDL_BlitSurface
+  // resolves to a per-row memcpy. Source has no colorkey on the cache
+  // path (caller pre-cleared the cache surface and rendered tiles into
+  // it; the result is opaque coverage).
+  if (!SDL_BlitSurface(src, NULL, _cached_window_surface, NULL))
+  {
+    LOG_ERROR("Renderer::drawCachedBackdrop: SDL_BlitSurface failed: {}",
+              SDL_GetError());
+    return false;
+  }
+
+  _bump_drawcall();
+  _record_dirty_rect(0, 0, screenWidth * scale, screenHeight * scale);
+  return true;
+}
+
 void Renderer::drawLine(int x1, int y1, int x2, int y2, NXColor color)
 {
   _DrawcallTimer _dct;  // patch 0060 — phase timing accumulator
diff --git a/src/graphics/Renderer.h b/src/graphics/Renderer.h
index c5fbd6d..523cf7b 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Renderer.h
+++ b/src/graphics/Renderer.h
@@ -86,6 +86,23 @@ class Renderer
 
     void blitPatternAcross(Surface *sfc, int x_dst, int y_dst, int y_src, int height);
 
+    // DOS-PORT (patch 0080, Phase 9 wave 17.2): single-call path that
+    // copies an already-rendered, screen-sized SDL_Surface (allocated +
+    // populated by map.cpp's backdrop cache) onto the window surface.
+    // Used to replace the per-frame ~80 drawSurface tile-loop in
+    // `map_draw_backdrop` with one same-format SDL_BlitSurface plus
+    // one full-screen dirty-rect record.
+    //
+    // Preconditions enforced at call time:
+    //   - src and _cached_window_surface non-NULL
+    //   - matching format and dimensions
+    //   - any queued slow-path renderer commands are flushed first
+    //     (matches _ensure_handrolled_surface's contract)
+    //
+    // Returns true if the blit ran; false on any precondition fail
+    // (caller must fall back to the live tile loop in that case).
+    bool drawCachedBackdrop(SDL_Surface *src);
+
     void clearScreen(NXColor color);
     void clearScreen(uint8_t r, uint8_t g, uint8_t b);
 
diff --git a/src/map.cpp b/src/map.cpp
index f17bb44..fb9ce37 100644
--- a/src/map.cpp
+++ b/src/map.cpp
@@ -20,6 +20,8 @@ using namespace NXE::Graphics;
 
 #include <json.hpp>
 #include <fstream>
+#include <climits>
+#include <cstdlib>  // getenv
 
 stMap map;
 
@@ -29,6 +31,76 @@ int num_stages;
 #define MAX_BACKDROPS 32
 Surface *backdrop[MAX_BACKDROPS];
 
+// DOS-PORT (patch 0080, Phase 9 wave 17.2): rendered-backdrop cache.
+// Holds a screen-sized SDL_Surface populated by the tile loop in
+// map_draw_backdrop's hot path. On a frame where the cache key matches
+// (same map, same backdrop_id, same scrolltype, same parscroll, same
+// indexed-mode), we skip the tile loop entirely and blit the cache to
+// the window in a single drawSurface-equivalent call (Renderer::
+// drawCachedBackdrop, patch 0080). On miss, we render tiles INTO the
+// cache surface (via raw SDL_BlitSurface — no Renderer overhead) and
+// then blit cache → window. Subsequent frames hit the cache.
+//
+// Wave-17.1 root cause this addresses: the per-frame ~80 drawSurface
+// tile-loop emits ~80 _record_dirty_rect calls whose union collapses
+// (via DIRTY_RECTS_MAX=16's cap-and-collapse step) into a single
+// screen-spanning bounding box every frame, tripping the dirty-path
+// threshold check so dirty_path_taken stays at 0. With a single
+// drawcall per frame the dirty rect is still full-screen — that
+// doesn't fix dirty-path engagement — but the per-call accounting
+// overhead AND the bg-layer drawcall count drop ~80x.
+//
+// Killswitch: SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_BACKDROP_CACHE=0 disables. Default ON.
+// Strict "0" match (per env-var convention).
+static SDL_Surface *g_backdrop_cache_sfc = nullptr;
+static int g_backdrop_cache_curmap     = -1;
+static int g_backdrop_cache_id         = -1;
+static int g_backdrop_cache_scrolltype = -1;
+static int g_backdrop_cache_parscroll_x = INT_MIN;
+static int g_backdrop_cache_parscroll_y = INT_MIN;
+static int g_backdrop_cache_indexed    = -1;
+static int g_backdrop_cache_w          = 0;
+static int g_backdrop_cache_h          = 0;
+static SDL_PixelFormat g_backdrop_cache_format = SDL_PIXELFORMAT_UNKNOWN;
+static int  g_backdrop_cache_disabled  = -1;  // -1=undecided, 0=on, 1=off
+
+// DOS-PORT (patch 0080): probe killswitch once on first call. Strict
+// "0" match disables the cache (lets a real-HW iter reproduce wave-9
+// pre-cache behavior for ablation). All other values keep the
+// optimization on.
+static bool _backdrop_cache_is_disabled()
+{
+  if (g_backdrop_cache_disabled < 0)
+  {
+    const char *e = std::getenv("SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_BACKDROP_CACHE");
+    g_backdrop_cache_disabled = (e && e[0] == '0' && e[1] == 0) ? 1 : 0;
+    LOG_INFO("map: backdrop cache {} (set SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_BACKDROP_CACHE=0 to disable)",
+             g_backdrop_cache_disabled ? "DISABLED (killswitch)" : "ENABLED (default)");
+  }
+  return g_backdrop_cache_disabled == 1;
+}
+
+// DOS-PORT (patch 0080): release the cache surface and reset all key
+// fields. Called by map_flush_graphics() (mode change) so the cache
+// doesn't outlive the backdrop[] surfaces it was rendered from.
+static void _backdrop_cache_reset()
+{
+  if (g_backdrop_cache_sfc)
+  {
+    SDL_DestroySurface(g_backdrop_cache_sfc);
+    g_backdrop_cache_sfc = nullptr;
+  }
+  g_backdrop_cache_curmap = -1;
+  g_backdrop_cache_id = -1;
+  g_backdrop_cache_scrolltype = -1;
+  g_backdrop_cache_parscroll_x = INT_MIN;
+  g_backdrop_cache_parscroll_y = INT_MIN;
+  g_backdrop_cache_indexed = -1;
+  g_backdrop_cache_w = 0;
+  g_backdrop_cache_h = 0;
+  g_backdrop_cache_format = SDL_PIXELFORMAT_UNKNOWN;
+}
+
 // for FindObject--finding NPC's by ID2
 Object *ID2Lookup[65536];
 
@@ -663,6 +735,106 @@ void map_draw_backdrop(void)
     //        mapy+=64;
   }
 
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0080, Phase 9 wave 17.2): cached-backdrop fast path.
+  // The tile-loop below is unchanged, but on a cache HIT we skip it
+  // entirely and blit the pre-rendered cache to the window. On a MISS
+  // we render the tile loop INTO the cache surface (raw SDL_BlitSurface
+  // — no Renderer overhead) and then blit cache → window. The cache
+  // key invalidates on map / backdrop / scrolltype / parscroll / format
+  // / indexed-mode change. Disabling via SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_BACKDROP_CACHE=0
+  // falls through to the original tile-loop path.
+  Renderer *r = Renderer::getInstance();
+  SDL_Surface *win = r->_cached_window_surface;
+  const int cache_indexed = r->indexedMode() ? 1 : 0;
+
+  if (!_backdrop_cache_is_disabled() && win && backdrop[map.backdrop])
+  {
+    SDL_Surface *bg_src = backdrop[map.backdrop]->surfaceCpu();
+    if (bg_src && bg_src->format == win->format)
+    {
+      // Cache key match check — if all dimensions/keys agree, single blit.
+      const bool cache_hit =
+          g_backdrop_cache_sfc &&
+          g_backdrop_cache_curmap     == game.curmap &&
+          g_backdrop_cache_id         == map.backdrop &&
+          g_backdrop_cache_scrolltype == map.scrolltype &&
+          g_backdrop_cache_parscroll_x == map.parscroll_x &&
+          g_backdrop_cache_parscroll_y == map.parscroll_y &&
+          g_backdrop_cache_indexed    == cache_indexed &&
+          g_backdrop_cache_w          == win->w &&
+          g_backdrop_cache_h          == win->h &&
+          g_backdrop_cache_format     == win->format;
+
+      if (cache_hit && r->drawCachedBackdrop(g_backdrop_cache_sfc))
+      {
+        return;  // single drawcall + dirty rect recorded; done.
+      }
+
+      // MISS — (re)allocate cache surface if dims/format changed.
+      if (!g_backdrop_cache_sfc ||
+          g_backdrop_cache_w != win->w ||
+          g_backdrop_cache_h != win->h ||
+          g_backdrop_cache_format != win->format)
+      {
+        if (g_backdrop_cache_sfc)
+        {
+          SDL_DestroySurface(g_backdrop_cache_sfc);
+          g_backdrop_cache_sfc = nullptr;
+        }
+        g_backdrop_cache_sfc = SDL_CreateSurface(win->w, win->h, win->format);
+        if (g_backdrop_cache_sfc &&
+            win->format == SDL_PIXELFORMAT_INDEX8 &&
+            r->masterPalette())
+        {
+          SDL_SetSurfacePalette(g_backdrop_cache_sfc, r->masterPalette());
+        }
+        g_backdrop_cache_w = win->w;
+        g_backdrop_cache_h = win->h;
+        g_backdrop_cache_format = win->format;
+      }
+
+      if (g_backdrop_cache_sfc)
+      {
+        // Render tiles directly into the cache surface — same loop
+        // structure as below, but SDL_BlitSurface (raw, no Renderer
+        // overhead, no per-call dirty-rect record). Bg sources have
+        // no colorkey for the cacheable scrolltypes hit here so a
+        // pre-clear isn't required for correctness, but doing one
+        // first guarantees deterministic content if backdrop tiles
+        // ever shrink past the screen edge.
+        SDL_FillSurfaceRect(g_backdrop_cache_sfc, NULL, 0);
+        SDL_Rect dst;
+        dst.w = w * r->scale;
+        dst.h = h * r->scale;
+        for (y = 0; y < r->screenHeight + map.parscroll_y; y += h)
+        {
+          for (x = 0; x < r->screenWidth + map.parscroll_x; x += w)
+          {
+            dst.x = (x - map.parscroll_x) * r->scale;
+            dst.y = (y - map.parscroll_y) * r->scale;
+            SDL_BlitSurface(bg_src, NULL, g_backdrop_cache_sfc, &dst);
+          }
+        }
+        // Update key + blit cache to window via the new helper.
+        g_backdrop_cache_curmap     = game.curmap;
+        g_backdrop_cache_id         = map.backdrop;
+        g_backdrop_cache_scrolltype = map.scrolltype;
+        g_backdrop_cache_parscroll_x = map.parscroll_x;
+        g_backdrop_cache_parscroll_y = map.parscroll_y;
+        g_backdrop_cache_indexed    = cache_indexed;
+        if (r->drawCachedBackdrop(g_backdrop_cache_sfc))
+        {
+          return;
+        }
+        // Else fall through to the live tile loop (cache blit failed
+        // — invalidate key so we don't claim a hit next frame).
+        g_backdrop_cache_curmap = -1;
+      }
+    }
+  }
+
+  // Fallback: original tile loop (cache disabled, allocation failed,
+  // window/bg format mismatch, or drawCachedBackdrop returned false).
   for (y = 0; y < Renderer::getInstance()->screenHeight + map.parscroll_y; y += h)
   {
     for (x = 0; x < Renderer::getInstance()->screenWidth + map.parscroll_x; x += w)
@@ -725,6 +897,13 @@ void map_flush_graphics()
 {
   int i;
 
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0080, Phase 9 wave 17.2): release the rendered-
+  // backdrop cache before deleting the backdrop[] surfaces so the cache
+  // doesn't outlive its source. Cache is keyed on backdrop_id which
+  // makes a stale cache after surface reload technically detectable,
+  // but explicit reset is cheaper than depending on key invariants.
+  _backdrop_cache_reset();
+
   for (i = 0; i < MAX_BACKDROPS; i++)
   {
     delete backdrop[i];
